description:
Hi,
I'm using virtuoso 7.1.
To see th problem just scroll to query results in last part.
Given following graph:
@prefix : <http://example.com/data/> .
@prefix base: <http://example.com/> .

base:graphTraversal
{

:A
    a :Concept ;
    :name "Concept A";
    :to  :AA1;
    :to  :AA2.

:A1
    a :Concept ;
    :to :A1A3;
    :name "Concept A1".

:A2
    a :Concept ;
    :to :A2A5;
    :name "Concept A2".

:AA1
    a :Property ;
    :to :A1;
    :cost 1.

:AA2
    a :Property ;
    :to :A2;
    :cost 20.

:A3
    a :Concept ;
    :to :A3A5;
    :name "Concept A3".

:A1A3
    a :Property ;
    :to :A3;
    :cost 7.

:A5
    a :Concept ;
    :name "Concept A5".

:A2A5
    a :Property ;
    :to :A5;
    :cost 1.

:A3A5
    a :Property ;
    :to :A5;
    :cost 1.

}

and query:
SELECT
?path as ?pathId
SUM(?cost) as ?pathCost
max(?cost) as ?pathMaxCost
max(?dist) as ?maxDistance
count(*) as ?elementsInPath
SUM(?dist) as ?totalDistance
WHERE
{
        graph <http://example.com/graphTraversal>
        {
                {
                        SELECT ?s ?target ?cost
                        WHERE
                        {

                                ?s <http://example.com/data/to> ?target.
                                optional { ?s <http://example.com/data/cost>?cost }

                        }

                }
                OPTION ( TRANSITIVE,
                # t_distinct,
                t_direction 1,
                t_in(?s),
                t_out(?target),
                t_min (0),
                t_max (16),
                t_step ('path_id') as ?path,
                t_step ('step_no') as ?dist ) .
                FILTER (?s= <http://example.com/data/A> && ?target = <http://example.com/data/A5> )
        }
}

GROUP BY ?path

I get the results:
pathId  pathCost    pathMaxCost     maxDistance     elementsInPath     totalDistance
1             0               20                    6                   7                           21
0             30              20                    4                   5                           10

but without grouping:
s                         target                      cost  path dist
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5      0   0
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5      0   1
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5  20  0   2
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5      0   3
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5  1   0   4
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5      1   0
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5      1   1
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5  1   1   2
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5      1   3
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5  7   1   4
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5      1   5
http://example.com/data/A   http://example.com/data/A5  1   1   6

So it seems ?pathCost/?pathMaxCost is not per path agregate, but total.
(for path 0 cost is 21, for path 1 is 9)
In contrast ?maxDistance, ?elementsInPath work fine per path agregate.
Also changing "t_direction 1" to "t_direction 3" randomly returns a ?pathMaxCost of "-4539628321310244864".
Update:
If ?name is added as an optional to inner select:
 SELECT ?s ?target ?cost ?name
                        WHERE
                        {

                                ?s <http://example.com/data/to> ?target.
                                optional {?s <http://example.com/data/name> ?name}
                                optional {?s <http://example.com/data/cost>?cost }

                        }

then the result(without grouping) removes some values from ?cost column (instead of 20,1,1,7,1 i get 20,1)
